    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three blocks, labeled, from left to right, A, B, and C, in contact with each other on a horizontal surface. Block B has an additional small block on top of it. Block B is smaller than block A, which is smaller than block C. Force F pushes rightward into the left side of block A.\" src=\"/images/bb3c5573fab858ab3bbbf5504242589d.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three large blocks, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>C</mtext></math></span></span>, and a small block attached to Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> slide across a horizontal surface as a constant force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span> is exerted on Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. There is negligible friction between the blocks and the horizontal surface. Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> pushes Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> with a force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A B\"><math alttext=\"F sub A B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>AB</mtext></msub></math></span></span>. The small block is then removed from Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> and attached to Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>C</mtext></math></span></span> and the same force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span> is exerted on Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span>. How does <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A B\"><math alttext=\"F sub A B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>AB</mtext></msub></math></span></span> compare in the second situation to the first situation and why?</p>\n",
